-- Guinea’s Opposition Groups Call on Citizens to Strike Monday
-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 2012-02-11T20:38:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-11/guinea-s-opposition-groups-call-on-citizens-to-strike-monday.html
Two groups of opposition parties in
 Guinea  called on the West African nation’s citizens to strike
nationwide on Feb. 13 and not report to work, according to a
statement from the groups today.  The decision was made “to express our displeasures against
repeated violations of human rights and fundamental liberties”
by those in power, le Collectif and Alliance Pour La Democratie
et le Progres said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ougna Camara in Conakry via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  